35.ezboard.com/usorfai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sorfai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 7:49:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2126.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> post 50 skill in stealth?</span><hr size=1> i have seen a post in somewhere else asked, if a 50 assassin with 50 skill in stealth, is there any bonus in hiding from an opponent for putting + stealth items on.<br><br>my question are:<br>1) is it possible to have skill excesses 50?<br>2) if so, will your post 50 skill gives stealthing bonus?<br><br>thx for you guys highbies to answer my questions<br><br>sor 30 inf on igraine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unarayanflatlander.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Narayan Flatlander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 8:18:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2126.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: post 50 skill in stealth?</span><hr size=1> 1) Yes<br><br>2) a friend SB had her character corruped and a Dev, came to re-create the character. He told her that skills over level DON'T do anything.<br><br><br>Just what I've been told... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 11:53:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2126.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: post 50 skill in stealth?</span><hr size=1> No, having stealth over 50 in RvR will not help you hide from enemy players better.  Once your stealth is equal to or higher than the level of the person, you are able to be seen within the minimum detect radius, approximately one horse length.  Stealth higher than the person's level does not reduce this radius in all tests that I've performed since 1.45 patch.<br><br>The effects on PvE are untested (i.e. how it affects mobs, if stealth is over your level). <p>-- Huff McTuff, 40 Nightshade, Pendragon<br>-- <i>Nightshade Team Lead</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 12:51:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2126.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: post 50 skill in stealth?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>2) a friend SB had her character corruped and a Dev, came to re-create the character. He told her that skills over level DON'T do anything.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Ok, so I don't know why the devs would say this, so I assume it was some kind of miscommunication within Mythic that has continued to be propigated.<br><br>Both this and the &quot;skill over 50 does nothing&quot; ideas could cause lots of problems for DAOC.<br><br>Everything I have read agrees with what Squink says about Stealth and having Stealth over 50. I don't know about over your level though.<br><br>Back to the quote... My Hero is 44. He is maxed in Large Weapons. With his epic and one +2 LW item, he is at 50 in Large Weapons. He goes and wacks a mob for 333 Damage. He then barrows and item from his friend, another +2 LW bracer. His skill in LW is now 52. He goes and wacks another mob, this time he does 336 damage. Both of them are his maximum possible hits, repeated over and over with consistant values. <br><br><br>The dev's seem to be mistaken on this or they are being misquoted, however I seem to recall them making the claims as well. Obviously as you can see having skill over level does indeed &quot;do something.&quot;<br><br>We see that except for a few classes (like Nightshades) having skill not be able to exceed your level and/or exceed 50 would be very detremental to the game. <br><br>How it is now, my Hero can get 50 LW, 50 CS, and 28 Parry. If Realm Ranks and Items capped you at level 50, then no one would need to spec more than 39 in anything, he could be 39LW, 39 Shield, 39 Blunt, 35 Parry. That would make him very powerful after realm ranks and +skill items. <br><br>I think it would turn everyone into carbon copies. We would all be the same within a class.  <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A> at: 2/12/02 12:56:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravnnevermoor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravn Nevermoor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 10:00:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2126.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: post 50 skill in stealth?</span><hr size=1> As of now with the frigged up detect hidden, the answer would be NO! I can see Vesper(a nightshade with 60+ skill) from a 10ft distance and that's with a 57 stealth of my own(that's with items and RP bonus). We also did a little testing and come to find out a level 30ish assassin can see a level 50 assassin while stealthed from the same distance as the 50 could see the 30. Hmmmm, is Mythic screwing us with our class like VI did? <p>Ravn Nevermoor<Br>40ish infiltrator of Aeonian Prophecy<Br>57 rogue of Legendary</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2126.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2126.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2126.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=2126.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Comman